postcontent:
SOLD-From my personal collection: A Mauser built from original parts by Federal Ordnance with a Federal Ordnance reciever. $350 Firm. No Trades.

The receiver is newly manufactured with "model 98/85" above an attractive American Eagle crest. The bolt sleeve is German mfg. as it contains a German serial number. The stock is new and appears to be Birchwood. The sling looks to be original German mfg. The sling buckle appears to have a Persian proof mark. Because of the German proof marks on the barrel, it appears to be late year FN mfg. The barrel is bright and looks strong. This is not a barrel that saw WWII action. It is a post WWII barrel. On the top of the barrel is a proof mark "K" under a star, below the K mark is a crown over "E" over "LG" over a star.
